pageTitle: Itinerary for Wednesday, April 27, 2016 | Prime Minister of Canada
articleHtml:
Itinerary for the Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, for Wednesday, April 27, 2016:

Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

10:00 a.m. The Prime Minister will visit Oskayak High School and will meet with students from the Aboriginal Youth Entrepreneurship Program (AYEP). He will then hold a media availability and will participate in a Q&A session with students.

Oskayak High School
919 Broadway Avenue
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

Notes for media:

  • Media should arrive no later than 9:30 a.m.
  • Photo opportunity for Oskayak High School visit and meeting with AYEP students
  • Open coverage for media availability
  • Open coverage for Q&A session with students

2:00 p.m. The Prime Minister will meet with students from the YWCA Trade Journey program.

Trade Journey
1320 Alberta Avenue
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

Notes for media:

  • Media should arrive no later than 1:30 p.m.
  • Photo opportunity only

5:15 p.m. The Prime Minister will meet with Saskatchewan Premier Brad Wall.

Delta Bessborough Hotel
601 Spadina Crescent East
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

Notes for media:

  • Media should arrive no later than 4:45 p.m.
  • Photo opportunity only

Please note: all times are local

PMO Media Relations:
Media@pmo-cpm.gc.ca
613-957-5555
